==Impact on Public View of Autism==
Since autism is either:

#A horrible, crippling brain disorder, or
#[[Nothing]]

There are not enough words for [[stupid]] in the English language to describe Aspies for Freedom's self-defeating goal of [[oxymoron|"promoting an accurate yet positive image of autism"]].  In particular, their core [[fantasy|belief]] that their disease-not-a-disease somehow makes them creative geniuses makes no goddamn sense at all, as such leading Asspie "talents" as obsession  with routine, rigid thought patterns and total literal-mindedness [[Captain Obvious|are the exact opposite of creativity]].  The one thing Asspies ''are'' good at, however, is relentless repetition, and so their [[cult|dedicated]] promotion of the [[meaningless noise|mantra]] [[circular logic|"autism makes you clever because clever people are autistic because autism makes you clever"]] has managed to <s>hypnotize</s> convince [[gullible|some sections of the public]]. 

The result of having this [[bullshit|highly sanitised]] view of autism is that when these people actually meet Asspies and witness their epically retarded behaviour, they ''always'' refuse to believe they're the real thing and accuse them of faking it.  (Which, of course, they usually are.)  

Meanwhile, as AFF's [[attention whoring]] continues to make it clear just how [[fucktard|obnoxious]] Asspies can really be, more and more people are coming to see the need for [[eugenics]].

